about.summary: A simple to use summary function that can be used with pipes and displays nicely in the console. The default summary statistics may be  modified by the user as can the default formatting. Support for data frames  and vectors is included, and users can implement their own skim methods for specific object types as described in a vignette. Default summaries include support for inline spark graphs. Instructions for managing these on  specific operating systems are given in the "Using skimr" vignette and the  README.

name: r-skimr
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.0.5" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-skimr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/skimr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/skimr/skimr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 15cf1df479a4f78c184ab780895e2f5e645b72b84dd3465cf0bbcc9745ef5a18

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-dplyr >=0.7
    - r-knitr >=1.2
    - r-magrittr
    - r-pander
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr >=1.1
    - r-tibble >=0.6
    - r-tidyr >=0.7
    - r-tidyselect >=0.2.4
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-dplyr >=0.7
    - r-knitr >=1.2
    - r-magrittr
    - r-pander
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr >=1.1
    - r-tibble >=0.6
    - r-tidyr >=0.7
    - r-tidyselect >=0.2.4

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('skimr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('skimr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ropenscilabs/skimr
  license: GPL-3
  summary: A simple to use summary function that can be used with pipes and displays nicely in
    the console. The default summary statistics may be  modified by the user as can
    the default formatting. Support for data frames  and vectors is included, and users
    can implement their own skim methods for specific object types as described in a
    vignette. Default summaries include support for inline spark graphs. Instructions
    for managing these on  specific operating systems are given in the "Using skimr"
    vignette and the  README.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
